      Methods in io.azam.ulidj with parameters of type ULID 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      static int ULID.compare​(ULID a, ULID b)
      Compares two ULID instances lexicographically.

      If the two ULID instances share a common prefix, then the lexicographic comparison is the result of comparing the rest of the value of the two ULID instances.

      A null ULID instance reference is considered lexicographically less than a non-null ULID instance reference.

      The comparison is consistent with equals, where the ULID instances are equal if and only if they are lexicographically equal.
      int ULID.compareTo​(ULID obj)
      Compares ULID instance lexicographically.

      If the two ULID instances share a common prefix, then the lexicographic comparison is the result of comparing the rest of the value of the two ULID instances.

      A null ULID instance reference is considered lexicographically less than a non-null ULID instance reference.

      Two null ULID instances references are considered equal.

      The comparison is consistent with equals, where the ULID instances are equal if and only if they are lexicographically equal.
